# =============================================================================
# Bavly KYC — Frontend (Vite) environment
# =============================================================================
#
# Local: copy to `.env` — variables must be prefixed VITE_ to appear in the bundle.
#
# Vercel: leave Project Root Directory empty; see repo root vercel.json + api/v1/[...slug].js.
#   Project → Settings → Environment Variables → Production (and Preview if needed)
#   Name:  VITE_API_BASE_URL
#   Value: https://YOUR-PUBLIC-API-HOST/api/v1   (HTTPS, no trailing slash)
#   Then Redeploy. On the API host set CORS_ORIGINS to your Vercel origin, e.g.
#   https://project-w8zqj.vercel.app — comma-separated, no spaces.
#
# Production build:
#   - `npm run build` reads VITE_API_BASE_URL from env first, then `.env`.
#   - Docker: docker build --build-arg VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com/api/v1 -t kyc-web .
#
# VPS / same host as API (nginx يوجّه /api/v1 إلى FastAPI):
#   اترك السطر معطّلاً أو فارغاً — الواجهة تستخدم تلقائياً `/api/v1` بنفس أصل الصفحة.
#   لا تضع http://localhost:8000 في build يُفتح من IP أو نطاق؛ المتصفح لن يصل إلى جهازك المحلي.
#
# The URL must be reachable from the **browser** (not localhost for a public Vercel site).
# =============================================================================

# محلي فقط — للإنتاج على خادم واحد مع nginx اترك هذا السطر معطلاً
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000/api/v1
